name: TC_f
group_concat(comment): Total carbon flux of the sinking fraction operationally defined as particles <350 um. The carbon measured in all process blanks from the five cruises was averaged to determine the mean process blank in sediment trap tubes for the field program (0.11 +/-0.2 mg C). This mean process blank was subtracted from the total carbon measured in each trap sample, and the result was divided by the trap collection area (0.0113 m^2) and the deployment length to yield flux. Reported fluxes are the mean of measurements from 2 or 3 tubes.
